1000 void MmwDemo_CfgUpdate(void *srcPtr, uint32_t offset, uint32_t size, int8_t subFrameNum)
1001 {
1002  /* if subFrameNum undefined, broadcast to all sub-frames */
1003  if(subFrameNum == MMWDEMO_SUBFRAME_NUM_FRAME_LEVEL_CONFIG)
1004  {
1005  uint8_t indx;
1006  for(indx = 0; indx < RL_MAX_SUBFRAMES; indx++)
1007  {
1008  memcpy((void *)((uint32_t) &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[indx] + offset), srcPtr, size);
1009  MmwDemo_setSubFramePendingState(&gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[indx], offset);
1010  }
1011  }
1012  else
1013  {
1014  /* Apply configuration to specific subframe (or to position zero for the legacy case
1015  where there is no advanced frame config) */
1016  memcpy((void *)((uint32_t) &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[subFrameNum] + offset), srcPtr, size);
1017  MmwDemo_setSubFramePendingState(&gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[subFrameNum], offset);
1018  }
1019 }

1079 static void MmwDemo_transmitProcessedOutput
1080 (
1081  UART_Handle uartHandle,
1082  DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *result,
1083  MmwDemo_output_message_stats *timingInfo
1084 )
1085 {
1086  MmwDemo_output_message_header header;
1087  MmwDemo_GuiMonSel *pGuiMonSel;
1088  MmwDemo_SubFrameCfg *subFrameCfg;
1089  uint32_t tlvIdx = 0;
1090  uint32_t index;
1091  uint32_t numPaddingBytes;
1092  uint32_t packetLen;
1093  uint8_t padding[MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN];
1094  MmwDemo_output_message_tl tl[MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_MAX];
1095  int32_t errCode;
1096  uint16_t *detMatrix = (uint16_t *)result->detMatrix.data;
1097  DPIF_PointCloudCartesian *objOut;
1098  cmplx16ImRe_t *azimuthStaticHeatMap;
1099  DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo *objOutSideInfo;
1100  DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats *stats;
1101 
1102  /* Get subframe configuration */
1103  subFrameCfg = &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[result->subFrameIdx];
1104 
1105  /* Get Gui Monitor configuration */
1106  pGuiMonSel = &subFrameCfg->guiMonSel;
1107 
1108  /* Clear message header */
1109  memset((void *)&header, 0, sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_header));
1110 
1111  /******************************************************************
1112  Send out data that is enabled, Since processing results are from DSP,
1113  address translation is needed for buffer pointers
1114  *******************************************************************/
1115  {
1116  detMatrix = (uint16_t *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)detMatrix,
1117  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
1118  &errCode);
1119  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)detMatrix!= SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
1120 
1121  objOut = (DPIF_PointCloudCartesian *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)result->objOut,
1122  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
1123  &errCode);
1124  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)objOut != SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
1125 
1126  objOutSideInfo = (DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)result->objOutSideInfo,
1127  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
1128  &errCode);
1129  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)objOutSideInfo != SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
1130 
1131  stats = (DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)result->stats,
1132  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
1133  &errCode);
1134  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)stats != SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
1135 
1136 
1137  result->radarCube.data = (void *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t) result->radarCube.data,
1138  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
1139  &errCode);
1140  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t) result->radarCube.data!= SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
1141  }
1142 
1143  /* Header: */
1144  header.platform = 0xA1642;
1145  header.magicWord[0] = 0x0102;
1146  header.magicWord[1] = 0x0304;
1147  header.magicWord[2] = 0x0506;
1148  header.magicWord[3] = 0x0708;
1149  header.numDetectedObj = result->numObjOut;
1150  header.version = MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUILD |
1151  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUGFIX << 8) |
1152  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MINOR << 16) |
1153  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MAJOR << 24);
1154 
1155  packetLen = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_header);
1156  if ((pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 1) || (pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 2) &&
1157  (result->numObjOut > 0))
1158  {
1159  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_DETECTED_POINTS;
1160  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudCartesian) * result->numObjOut;
1161  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1162  tlvIdx++;
1163  }
1164  /* Side info */
1165  if ((pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 1) && (result->numObjOut > 0))
1166  {
1167  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_DETECTED_POINTS_SIDE_INFO;
1168  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo) * result->numObjOut;
1169  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1170  tlvIdx++;
1171  }
1172  if (pGuiMonSel->logMagRange)
1173  {
1174  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_RANGE_PROFILE;
1175  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(uint16_t) * subFrameCfg->numRangeBins;
1176  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1177  tlvIdx++;
1178  }
1179  if (pGuiMonSel->noiseProfile)
1180  {
1181  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_NOISE_PROFILE;
1182  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(uint16_t) * subFrameCfg->numRangeBins;
1183  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1184  tlvIdx++;
1185  }
1186  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeAzimuthHeatMap)
1187  {
1188  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_AZIMUT_STATIC_HEAT_MAP;
1189  tl[tlvIdx].length = result->azimuthStaticHeatMapSize * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
1190  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1191  tlvIdx++;
1192  }
1193  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeDopplerHeatMap)
1194  {
1195  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_RANGE_DOPPLER_HEAT_MAP;
1196  tl[tlvIdx].length = subFrameCfg->numRangeBins * subFrameCfg->numDopplerBins * sizeof(uint16_t);
1197  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1198  tlvIdx++;
1199  }
1200  if (pGuiMonSel->statsInfo)
1201  {
1202  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_STATS;
1203  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_stats);
1204  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;

1567 static uint16_t MmwDemo_convertCfarToLinear(uint16_t codedCfarVal, uint8_t numVirtualAntennas)
1568 {
1569  uint16_t linearVal;
1570  float dbVal, linVal;
1571 
1572  /* dbVal is a float value from 0-100dB. It needs to
1573  be converted to linear scale..
1574  First, recover float dbVal that was encoded in CLI. */
1575  dbVal = (float)(codedCfarVal / MMWDEMO_CFAR_THRESHOLD_ENCODING_FACTOR);
1576 
1577  /* Now convert it to linear value according to the following:
1578  linear_value = dB_value * (256 / 6) * (numVirtualAntennas / (2^ ceil(log2(numVirtualAntennas)))) .
1579  */
1580  linVal = dbVal * (256.0 / 6.0) * ((float)numVirtualAntennas / (float)(1 << mathUtils_ceilLog2(numVirtualAntennas)));
1581 
1582  linearVal = (uint16_t) linVal;
1583  return (linearVal);
1584 }

1714 static int32_t MmwDemo_dataPathConfig (void)

1735  ptrCtrlCfg->u.advancedFrameCfg.frameCfg.frameSeq.numOfSubFrames;
1736  }
1737  else

1739  gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames = 1;
1740  }
1741 
1742  DebugP_log0("App: Issuing Pre-start Common Config IOCTL\n");
1743 
1744  /* Get RF frequency scale factor */
1745  gMmwMssMCB.rfFreqScaleFactor = SOC_getDeviceRFFreqScaleFactor(gMmwMssMCB.socHandle, &errCode);
1746  if (errCode < 0)

1761  goto exit;
1762  }
1763

1765 
1766  /* Reason for reverse loop is that when sensor is started, the first sub-frame
1767  * will be active and the ADC configuration needs to be done for that sub-frame
1768  * before starting (ADC buf hardware does not have notion of sub-frame, it will
1769  * be reconfigured every sub-frame). This cannot be alternatively done by calling
1770  * the MmwDemo_ADCBufConfig function only for the first sub-frame because this is
1771  * a utility API that computes the rxChanOffset that is part of ADC dataProperty
1772  * which will be used by range DPU and therefore this computation is required for
1773  * all sub-frames.
1774  */

1776  subFrameIndx--)

1779 
1780  /*****************************************************************************
1781  * Data path :: Algorithm Configuration
1782  *****************************************************************************/
1783 
1784  /* Parse the profile and chirp configs and get the valid number of TX Antennas */
1785  errCode = MmwDemo_RFParser_parseConfig(&RFparserOutParams, subFrameIndx,
1786  &gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg, ptrCtrlCfg,
1787  &subFrameCfg->adcBufCfg,
1788  gMmwMssMCB.rfFreqScaleFactor,
1789  subFrameCfg->bpmCfg.isEnabled);
1790

1794  goto exit;
1795  }

1798  * less than 16 (the minimal numDopplerBins supported in doppler DPU DSP).
1799  * In this case, interpolate to detect better with CFAR tuning. E.g. a 2 -pt FFT will
1800  * be problematic in terms of distinguishing direction of motion */
1801  if (RFparserOutParams.numDopplerChirps <= 8)
1802  {
1803  RFparserOutParams.dopplerStep = RFparserOutParams.dopplerStep / (16 / RFparserOutParams.numDopplerBins);
1804  RFparserOutParams.numDopplerBins = 16;

1814  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);

1823  subFrameCfg->numChirpsPerSubFrame = RFparserOutParams.numChirpsPerFrame;
1824 
1825  errCode = MmwDemo_ADCBufConfig(gMmwMssMCB.adcBufHandle,
1826  gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg.chCfg.rxChannelEn,
1827  subFrameCfg->numChirpsPerChirpEvent,

2014 static int32_t MmwDemo_eventCallbackFxn(uint16_t msgId, uint16_t sbId, uint16_t sbLen, uint8_t *payload)
2015 {
2016  uint16_t asyncSB = RL_GET_SBID_FROM_UNIQ_SBID(sbId);
2017 
2018  /* Process the received message: */
2019  switch (msgId)
2020  {
2021  case RL_RF_ASYNC_EVENT_MSG:
2022  {
2023  /* Received Asychronous Message: */
2024  switch (asyncSB)
2025  {
2026  case RL_RF_AE_CPUFAULT_SB:
2027  {
2028  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
2029  break;
2030  }
2031  case RL_RF_AE_ESMFAULT_SB:
2032  {
2033  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
2034  break;
2035  }
2036  case RL_RF_AE_ANALOG_FAULT_SB:
2037  {
2038  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
2039  break;
2040  }
2041  case RL_RF_AE_INITCALIBSTATUS_SB:
2042  {
2043  rlRfInitComplete_t* ptrRFInitCompleteMessage;
2044  uint32_t calibrationStatus;
2045 
2046  /* Get the RF-Init completion message: */
2047  ptrRFInitCompleteMessage = (rlRfInitComplete_t*)payload;
2048  calibrationStatus = ptrRFInitCompleteMessage->calibStatus & 0xFFFU;
2049 
2050  /* Display the calibration status: */
2051  CLI_write ("Debug: Init Calibration Status = 0x%x\n", calibrationStatus);
2052  break;
2053  }
2054  case RL_RF_AE_FRAME_TRIGGER_RDY_SB:
2055  {
2056  gMmwMssMCB.stats.frameTriggerReady++;
2057  break;
2058  }
2059  case RL_RF_AE_MON_TIMING_FAIL_REPORT_SB:

2061  gMmwMssMCB.stats.failedTimingReports++;
2062  break;
2063  }
2064  case RL_RF_AE_RUN_TIME_CALIB_REPORT_SB:

2066  gMmwMssMCB.stats.calibrationReports++;
2067  break;

2072  DebugP_log0("App: BSS stop (frame end) received\n");
2073 
2074  MmwDemo_dataPathStop();
2075  break;
2076  }
2077  default:
2078  {
2079  System_printf ("Error: Asynchronous Event SB Id %d not handled\n", asyncSB);
2080  break;
2081  }
2082  }
2083  break;
2084  }

2086  case RL_MMWL_ASYNC_EVENT_MSG:

2088  switch (asyncSB)
2089  {
2090  case RL_MMWL_AE_MISMATCH_REPORT:
2091  {
2092  /* link reports protocol error in the async report from BSS */
2093  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
2094  break;
2095  }
2096  case RL_MMWL_AE_INTERNALERR_REPORT:
2097  {
2098  /* link reports internal error during BSS communication */
2099  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
2100  break;
2101  }
2102  }
2103  break;
2104  }
2105  default:
2106  {
2107  System_printf ("Error: Asynchronous message %d is NOT handled\n", msgId);
2108  break;
2109  }
2110  }
2111  return 0;
2112 }

2668  currSubFrameStats = &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameStats[currSubFrameIdx];
2669  prevSubFrameStats = &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameStats[prevSubFrameIdx];
2670

2672  * Transmit results
2673  *****************************************************************/

2682  (DPU_AoAProc_compRxChannelBiasCfg *)SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)dpcResults->compRxChanBiasMeasurement,
2683  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
2684  &retVal);

2686 
2687  MmwDemo_measurementResultOutput(dpcResults->compRxChanBiasMeasurement);
2688  }
2689  else
2690  {
2691  /* DPC is not ready to ship the measurement results */
2692  }
2693  }
2694 
2695 
2696  /* Translate the address: */
2697  frameStats = (MmwDemo_output_message_stats *)SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)ptrResult->ptrBuffer[1],
2698  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
2699  &retVal);
2700  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)frameStats != SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
2701 
2702  /* Update current frame stats */
2703  currSubFrameStats->outputStats.interFrameCPULoad = frameStats->interFrameCPULoad;
2704  currSubFrameStats->outputStats.activeFrameCPULoad= frameStats->activeFrameCPULoad;
2705  currSubFrameStats->outputStats.interChirpProcessingMargin = frameStats->interChirpProcessingMargin;
2706  currSubFrameStats->outputStats.interFrameProcessingTime = frameStats->interFrameProcessingTime;
2707  prevSubFrameStats->outputStats.interFrameProcessingMargin = frameStats->interFrameProcessingMargin;
2708  currSubFrameStats->outputStats.interFrameProcessingMargin = currSubFrameStats->outputStats.interFrameProcessingMargin -
2709  (currSubFrameStats->pendingConfigProcTime + currSubFrameStats->subFramePreparationTime);
2710 
2711  if (gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[currSubFrameIdx].lvdsStreamCfg.dataFmt !=
2712  MMW_DEMO_LVDS_STREAM_CFG_DATAFMT_DISABLED)
2713  {
2714  /* check Edma errors (which are considered fatal) for the current sub-frame's
2715  * h/w session that is expected to be completed by now */
2716  MmwDemo_checkEdmaErrors();
2717 
2718  /* Pend for completion of h/w session, generally this will not wait
2719  * because of time spent doing inter-frame processing is expected to
2720  * be bigger than the transmission of the h/w session */
2721  Semaphore_pend(gMmwMssMCB.lvdsStream.hwFrameDoneSemHandle, BIOS_WAIT_FOREVER);
2722  }
2723 
2724  /* Transfer data on LVDS if s/w session is enabled for the current sub-frame */
2725  if(gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[currSubFrameIdx].lvdsStreamCfg.isSwEnabled == 1)
2726  {
2727  MmwDemo_transferLVDSUserData(currSubFrameIdx, dpcResults);
2728  }
2729

2731  MmwDemo_transmitProcessedOutput(gMmwMssMCB.loggingUartHandle,
2732  dpcResults,
2733  &currSubFrameStats->outputStats);
2734 
2735  /* Wait until s/w session is complete. We expect the LVDS transmission of
2736  * s/w session to be completed by now because the UART transmission above is slower.
2737  * Doing the wait immediately after starting the transmission above MmwDemo_transferLVDSUserData
2738  * will serialize the LVDS and UART transfers so it is better to do after UART
2739  * transmission (which is blocking call i.e UART transmission is completed when we exit
2740  * out of above MmwDemo_transmitProcessedOutput). Note we cannot replace below code
2741  * with check for previous sub-frame s/w session completion before the
2742  * MmwDemo_transferLVDSUserData above because we need to ensure that
2743  * current sub-frame/frame's contents are not being read during the
2744  * next sub-frame/frame transmission, presently the data that is being
2745  * transmitted is not double buffered to allow this */
2746  if(gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[currSubFrameIdx].lvdsStreamCfg.isSwEnabled == 1)
2747  {
2748  /* check Edma errors (which are considered fatal) for the s/w session
2749  * that is expected to be completed by now */
2750  MmwDemo_checkEdmaErrors();
2751 
2752  /* Pend completion of s/w session, no wait is expected here */
2753  Semaphore_pend(gMmwMssMCB.lvdsStream.swFrameDoneSemHandle, BIOS_WAIT_FOREVER);
2754  }
2755 
2756  /* Update current frame transmit time */
2757  currSubFrameStats->outputStats.transmitOutputTime = (Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime)/R4F_CLOCK_MHZ; /* In micro seconds */
2758 
2759 
2760  /*****************************************************************
2761  * Handle dynamic pending configuration
2762  * For non-advanced frame case:
2763  * process all pending dynamic config commands.
2764  * For advanced-frame case:
2765  * Process next sub-frame related pending dynamic config commands.
2766  * If the next sub-frame was the first sub-frame of the frame,
2767  * then process common (sub-frame independent) pending dynamic config
2768  * commands.
2769  *****************************************************************/
2770  startTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
2771 
2772  nextSubFrameIdx = MmwDemo_getNextSubFrameIndx(currSubFrameIdx, numSubFrames);
2773  retVal = MmwDemo_processPendingDynamicCfgCommands(nextSubFrameIdx);
2774  if (retVal != 0)
2775  {
2776  System_printf ("Error: Executing Pending Dynamic Configuration Commands [Error code %d]\n",
2777  retVal);
2778  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
2779  }
2780  currSubFrameStats->pendingConfigProcTime = (Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime)/R4F_CLOCK_MHZ;
2781 
2782  /*****************************************************************
2783  * Prepare for subFrame switch
2784  *****************************************************************/
2785  if(numSubFrames > 1)
2786  {
2787  MmwDemo_SubFrameCfg *nextSubFrameCfg;
2788  uint16_t dummyRxChanOffset[SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL];
2789 
2790  startTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
2791 
2792  nextSubFrameCfg = &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[nextSubFrameIdx];
2793 
2794  /* Configure ADC for next sub-frame */
2795  retVal = MmwDemo_ADCBufConfig(gMmwMssMCB.adcBufHandle,
2796  gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg.chCfg.rxChannelEn,
2797  nextSubFrameCfg->numChirpsPerChirpEvent,
2798  nextSubFrameCfg->adcBufChanDataSize,
2799  &nextSubFrameCfg->adcBufCfg,
2800  &dummyRxChanOffset[0]);
2801  if(retVal < 0)
2802  {
2803  System_printf("Error: ADCBuf config failed with error[%d]\n", retVal);
2804  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
2805  }
2806 
2807  /* Configure HW LVDS stream for this subframe? */
2808  if(nextSubFrameCfg->lvdsStreamCfg.dataFmt != MMW_DEMO_LVDS_STREAM_CFG_DATAFMT_DISABLED)
2809  {
2810  /* check Edma errors (which are considered fatal) for any previous session, even
2811  * though we have checked for a previous s/w session, if s/w session weren't
2812  * enabled, then this will check for previous h/w session related Edma errors */
2813  MmwDemo_checkEdmaErrors();
2814 
2815  MmwDemo_configLVDSHwData(nextSubFrameIdx);
2816  }
2817 
2818  currSubFrameStats->subFramePreparationTime = (Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime)/R4F_CLOCK_MHZ;
2819  }
2820  else
2821  {
2822  currSubFrameStats->subFramePreparationTime = 0;
2823  }
2824 
2825  /*****************************************************************
2826  * Send notification to data path after results are handled
2827  *****************************************************************/
2828  /* Indicate result consumed and end of frame/sub-frame processing */
2829  exportInfo.subFrameIdx = currSubFrameIdx;
2830  retVal = DPM_ioctl (gMmwMssMCB.objDetDpmHandle,
2831  DPC_OBJDET_IOCTL__DYNAMIC_EXECUTE_RESULT_EXPORTED,
2832  &exportInfo,
2833  sizeof (DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResultExportedInfo));
2834  if (retVal < 0) {
2835  System_printf ("Error: DPM DPC_OBJDET_IOCTL__DYNAMIC_EXECUTE_RESULT_EXPORTED failed [Error code %d]\n",
2836  retVal);
2837  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
2838  }
